HEADWORD: Lanolin
<hw>Lan"o*lin</hw> <pr>(l⟦acr⟧n"⟦osl⟧*l⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>lana</ets> wool + <ets>ole</ets>um oil.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A peculiar fatlike body, made up of
cholesterin and certain fatty acids, found in feathers, hair, wool, and
keratin tissues generally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Under the same name, it is prepared from wool for
commercial purposes, and forms an admirable basis for ointments, being
readily absorbed by the skin.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lansah</ent>⟦br⟧
